tourBios.carHigh:
2014: Finished T5 at Web.com Tour Q-School in December. Shot 65 to take first-round lead. Second-round 77 dropped him to T45. Rebounded with another 65 on the third day before closing with 69-68-69..Member of 2014 European Tour and 2014 Challenge Tour. Got four starts on European Tour, making all four cuts, with best showing a T12 at the Najeti Hotels et Golf in June. Other finishes were T24, T24 and T39.

2013: Played in three Web.com Tour events but missed the cut in all three.

2012: Made two Web.com Tour starts. Finished T46 at the Neediest Kids Championship.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Was the 2010 NCAA Div. III national champion and was also a NCAA Div. III four-time All-American. Won the 2010 Jack Nicklaus Award given to the top Div. III golfer.
tourBios.personal: Was born in Maryland and lived in Cincinnati before moving to California...Fond golf memory is playing golf with his dad on cold winter days in Cincinnati...If not a professional golfer, would be an entrepreneur...Favorite course played is Pete Dye GC...Biggest thrill outside golf was spending time at an orphanage in Mexico.
